OL,3,CAsian family 'targeted' in Hartlepool
OL,4,Cdisorder will now leave the town
OL,6,FWhen asked if he was scared, he said:
OL,7,F"I was more worried about my mum."
OL,9,FHe said they have lived in the
OL,10,Fproperty for two years and that he
OL,11,F"recognised faces" of those inside of
OL,12,Fhis house.
OL,14,FThe man is now planning to leave
OL,15,FHartlepool for good and in a bid to
OL,16,Ffind somewhere he believes is safe for
OL,17,Fhis mother.
